title: L.A. Drops Criminal Charges Against Election Software Executive
description: Eugene Yu was accused of illegally sending data about poll workers to China, in a case that became fodder for election deniers.
dc:creator: Stuart A. Thompson

media:content.media:credit: Emily Elconin for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Before the arrest of its founder and chief executive, Eugene Yu, Konnech repeatedly denied keeping data outside the United States, including in statements to The New York Times.
